RACE.RACE_TEXT: SAM HOUSTON RACE PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 18000. (PLUS UP TO $3,060 ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 22. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BENDELENE stalked the leader from the four path, was inching up on the turn to gain command in the upper stretch and held on grudgingly to prevail in the end. LINGERING PROMISE lead the way from the inside by a head into the turn, then continued to bid in the stretch but was outbid by an outside rival and was second best. STORMIEIS BLUE raced closed behind the field while five wide then rallied in the upper stretch to close willingly for the show prize. TAYLOR'S SECRET raced in close while three wide to bid on the turn but came up evenly in the final furlongs. HOT TUB HOTTIE was in a strong bid while pressing the pace from the two path, was hard used on the turn and was out run in the end.

ENTRY.COMMENT: lead inside, bid upper stretch, second best

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied 2 wide, hard used turn, outrun

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 4w, gained lead 3/16, held on
